# Shipyard iOS — AI Coding Instructions

Read `CLAUDE.md` + `HANDOFF.md` first. This file is a short-form summary for tools that don't auto-load `CLAUDE.md`.

## Tech Stack
- SwiftUI + iOS 17 + `@Observable` + `@MainActor`
- No external deps in Phase 1 (no ClarityUI, no Supabase yet)
- Hand-crafted `Shipyard.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj` — UUID prefix `SY`
- Bundle ID: `com.chasewhittaker.Shipyard`

## Coding Style
- Pragmatic, no over-engineering, minimal comments
- Single store (`FleetStore`) injected via `.environment(store)`
- `nonisolated init()` so `@State private var store = FleetStore()` works in `@main`
- All data as `Codable` structs — never `[String: Any]`
- Field names stay snake_case on models (match web `Project` TS type for future Supabase decode)

## Nautical Lexicon (user-facing copy)
- Projects → **Ships**
- Fleet (not dashboard)
- Under Construction (not building)
- Launched (not shipped)
- Drydock (not paused)
- Captain's Log (not learnings)

## Phase 1 Scope
- Read-only fleet list from hardcoded mock data in `FleetStore.loadMockFleet()`
- No Supabase, no auth, no write ops
- Source of truth is `portfolio/shipyard/` (web) — mirror types + labels, don't invent

## Build
```bash
xcodebuild build -project Shipyard.xcodeproj -scheme Shipyard \
  -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 15' CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO
```
